Package: fireR
Title: Download and Load USGS Fire Data and EPA Ecoregion Boundaries
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Noah", "Weidig", email = "noah.weidig@ufl.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides fast, convenient access to USGS fire datasets, USFS
    Wildland-Urban Interface (WUI) data, and EPA/CEC ecoregion boundaries.
    For MTBS (Monitoring Trends in Burn Severity), downloads the composite
    burned-area extent shapefile and returns it as either an 'sf' or 'terra'
    SpatVector object with optional filtering by year and incident type. For
    the Southeast FireMap (SE FireMap), downloads Annual Burn Severity Mosaics
    as one ZIP per year (2000-2022) of predicted Composite Burn Index (CBI)
    values covering 78 ARD Landsat tiles across the southeastern United States,
    plus three single-file geodatabase ZIPs covering 1994-2024: Fire History,
    Burned Area Polygons, and Burned Area Rasters. Provides a downloader for the USFS WUI dataset (4.65 GB),
    which delineates areas where structures meet or intermingle with undeveloped
    wildland vegetation. Downloads and reads NIFC (National Interagency Fire
    Center) wildfire perimeters and the USFS Fire Occurrence Database (FPA-FOD,
    1992-2020), each with optional year filtering. Also provides loaders for Commission for Environmental
    Cooperation (CEC) North America ecoregion boundaries at Levels 1-3, and US
    EPA ecoregion boundaries at Levels 3-4 (with optional state boundaries).
